{
    "abstract": "Segment Routing (SR) allows a flexible definition of end-to-end paths within IGP topologies by encoding paths as sequences of topological subpaths called \"segments\".  These segments are advertised by the link-state routing protocols (IS-IS and OSPF).  This document describes the OSPFv3 extensions required for Segment Routing with the MPLS data plane. ",
